    <item>
      <title>Unofficial Linkle 3 Patcher</title>
      <author>i2m</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/441448</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/441448#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">a6b0baad489674ca5a9982db798778f126e6f78a</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 13 Sep 2024 22:53:38 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64542d66405a3.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64542d484d17d.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64528455b4f2b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64542d9e009a7.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64542ea1d1ee1.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6464e8371bab3.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Update:&lt;/strong&gt; Tool for UKMM&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;Small update that only adds a tool in the downloads section:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(226, 226, 226); font-family: Open\ Sans, sans-serif"&gt;If you're using &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" href="https://gamebanana.com/tools/12110"&gt;UKMM&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(226, 226, 226); font-family: Open\ Sans, sans-serif"&gt; instead of BCML, it may not accept the BNP files you get using the patcher. In that case, you can use the tool to repack the BNP for use on UKMM (see the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(226, 226, 226); font-family: Open\ Sans, sans-serif"&gt;new &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(226, 226, 226); font-family: Open\ Sans, sans-serif"&gt;section on the mod page for more instructions).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;* &lt;span style="color: rgb(226, 226, 226); font-family: Open\ Sans, sans-serif"&gt;Thanks to &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer nofollow" class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1698083"&gt;gingeravalanche&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(226, 226, 226); font-family: Open\ Sans, sans-serif"&gt; for the technical tips!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;* L&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(226, 226, 226); font-family: Open\ Sans, sans-serif"&gt;eave your feedback in the comments section; thanks!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreyColor"&gt;&lt;span style="color: rgb(226, 226, 226); font-family: Open\ Sans, sans-serif"&gt;* Please note the tool is a temporary solution, in beta stage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;DESCRIPTION&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;This mod fixes the &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Linkle 3 too long arms&lt;/span&gt; (especially noticeable using the &lt;u&gt;Girly Animation Pack&lt;/u&gt; mod) by patching the base skeleton using &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Linkle 2 body proportions&lt;/span&gt;. By doing this, all the Linkle 3 armors (the ones included in the mod, and also any third-party replacement or standalone new armors) will be forced to use these new body proportions.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;This mod also adds &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;backwards compatibility&lt;/span&gt; to Linkle 3, allowing to install &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Linkle 2 armor mods&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;without neck gap or skin texture issues (some mods may still have glitches and they will require to be edited by their authors).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;del&gt;Switch port &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/442814"&gt;available here&lt;/a&gt; - thanks to&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1874702"&gt;Cod3xDev&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/del&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Please note:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;Version 1&lt;/b&gt; of t&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i&gt;his mod is included in the &lt;b&gt;Girly Animation Pack&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;but in Lite form (it patches only the long arms issue and nothing else). If you want to install this mod to get the backwards compatibility, you don't need to uninstall the one in the Girly Animation Pack if already installed (installing this one will upgrade it). Also, you don't need the Girly Animation Pack if you are Ok with the current player animations.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;SETUP 1 - The patch program&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;Download &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;version 1&lt;/span&gt; or &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;version 2&lt;/span&gt; ZIP file&amp;nbsp;in a folder of your computer:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;· &lt;u&gt;Version 1&lt;/u&gt;: &lt;i&gt;The old good unofficial patch.&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Use it if version 2 is not working for you.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;· &lt;u&gt;Version 2&lt;/u&gt;: &lt;i&gt;The improved current version,&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;with a better backwards compatibility.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/i&gt;You can select &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;version 2A&lt;/span&gt; or&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;2B&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. The&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;i&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/i&gt;only difference is the &lt;u&gt;arms patch&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; - Versions 1 &amp;amp; 2A uses the one made by me,&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; - Version 2B has been made by&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1826204"&gt;EvanM0816&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/6464e8371bab3.jpg"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Unzip the downloaded file (using for example&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://www.7-zip.org/download.html" target="_blank"&gt;7z&lt;/a&gt;); and you will find there the program called&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;L3Patcher.exe&lt;/span&gt;, execute it (you need to use Microsoft Windows).&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;As you can see in the GIF below, you only need to &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;open BCML&lt;/span&gt;, select your &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Linkle 3&lt;/span&gt; installed mod on the list on the left, press the &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;blue folder Explore button&lt;/span&gt;, copy the &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;full path&lt;/span&gt; from the Windows explorer that will pop-up, and &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;paste it&lt;/span&gt; in the text box of the &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;L3Patcher&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;window.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;After that, just &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;press the &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;GO button&lt;/span&gt; to start copying the needed files, patching them, and finally packing them to get your custom &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Unofficial Linkle 3 Patch BNP file&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;ready to install in BCML as usual. &lt;i&gt;Please note I did my best to bring you a program that will work as flawlessly as possible, but as this is the first version, if you encounter any bug please report it in the comments section.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/how_to_patch.gif"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;SETUP 2 - Installing the mod&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;When you have the BNP file ready, just install it in BCML,&amp;nbsp;&lt;b&gt;AFTER&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Linkle 3&lt;/span&gt; or &lt;b&gt;AFTER&lt;/b&gt; &lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/49763"&gt;Girly Animation Pack&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;as usual. During the install, a window with several options will appear on BCML:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/64542d484d17d.jpg"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;LINKLE 3 LONG ARM FIX:&lt;/b&gt; This fix will be installed no matter if the option is checked or not; it's just informative.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;COMPATIBILITY WITH LINKLE 2 MODS:&lt;/b&gt; This one is informative too, and will be installed no matter if it's checked or not.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;SKIN TEXTURE FOR LINKLE 2 MODS: &lt;/b&gt;This one is optional (unchecked by default). Will replace the Linkle 3 upper base body texture with a less detailed one, but fully compatible with both Linkle 3 and Linkle 2 mods. This will allow any Linkle 2 mod to be installed without body skin texture issues.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;b&gt;HEADGEAR FIX FOR LINKLE 2 MODS&amp;nbsp;(&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Only on version 1, not needed on version 2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;):&lt;/b&gt; This will replace the Linkle 3 default Phantom Ganon skull, the Fierce Deity Mask, the Rubber Helm, the Dark Hood and the Salvager Headgear, and will add to them the missing neck that fills the gap when used with Linkle 2 armors (don't worry as this "new" neck will not be visible while wearing Linkle 3 armors). Thanks to&amp;nbsp;&lt;a class="Name" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1708955"&gt;Kitsen&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;for the feedback on this!&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Experimental&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;Support for UKMM&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;If you're using UKMM instead of BCML, please note it may not accept the BNP files you get using this patcher. Temporarily to solve this, I added a tool in the downloads section called&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Repack_BNP_for_UKMM.zip&lt;/span&gt;. Please note it's in beta stage. Please leave your feedback in the comments section. How to use it:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;ol&gt;&lt;li&gt;Get the BNP using the patcher as usual.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Download&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Repack_BNP_for_UKMM.zip&lt;/span&gt; and unzip it in a folder.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li class="SelectedElement"&gt;Execute the file&amp;nbsp;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;RepackBNPusing7z.exe&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in that folder.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Drop the BNP file over the program window and press the button.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;You will get the BNP repacked and (hopefully) compatible with UKMM.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;INCOMPATIBILITIES&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;This mod is replacing Linkle 3 base body file (hairstyle, head, face, upper and lower body) and will conflict with any other mod that changes the base body too (for example, a base hairstyle replacement). If you install the skin texture option, then it will conflict too with mods that are changing the color of the base body somehow (skin color, hair color, eyes color...).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;CHECK IF THE PATCH IT'S WORKING&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;The default idle on Linkle 3 has the hands very apart of the body, this will trick our mind and we will not see any difference with and without the patch installed. We will look at other idles/poses, for example the &lt;b&gt;defense stance&lt;/b&gt;, or when &lt;b&gt;starting walking&lt;/b&gt; for a second we get the hands in line with the body. Let's see:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;First animation:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="BlueColor"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Linkle 3 using defense stance.&lt;br&gt;Clearly arms are shorter now, no matter if we use patch 21a or 21b:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/example1.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;Second animation:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Linkle 3 when starts walking.&lt;br&gt;For a moment we get arms in line with the body, and we can confirm the patch is working:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/example2.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class="PurpleColor"&gt;Third animation:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span class="PurpleColor"&gt;Linkle 3 + Girly Animation Pack + Patch.&lt;br&gt;Girly mod has a very different default idle, with the arms in line with the body.&lt;br&gt;The patch is working no matter if we use the Lite patch included, or the full Patch.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;img src="https://files.gamebanana.com/bitpit/example3.apng"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;MODDERS RESOURCES&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;If you want to make your mod compatible with this patch, you could make use of parts of this mod once you get the patched BNP file (&lt;i&gt;please remember distributing Linkle 3 assets without autor's explicit permission could end in your mod trashed for Copyright infringement&lt;/i&gt;):&lt;br&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;From &lt;b&gt;TitleBG.pack&lt;/b&gt;, extract &lt;b&gt;LINK.SBFRES&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;and &lt;b&gt;ARMOR_DEFAULT.SBFRES&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;(the base body with the arm patch). Optional: &lt;b&gt;GAMEROMPLAYER.SBACTORPACK&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;for the upper body chest physics (without this file, you just won't get them).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;From &lt;b&gt;LINK.TEX1.SBFRES&lt;/b&gt; you can extract the base body skin texture &lt;b&gt;Link_Skin_Alb.png&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;that looks good in Linke 3 and also in Linkle 2 mods (the ones that rely in the base body texture).&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;QUESTIONS &amp;amp; ANSWERS&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Q: &lt;/b&gt;Why this patch?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;A: &lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;The Unofficial Linkle 3 mod was trashed by the Linkle 3 owner for copyright infringement. That is, for distributing Linkle 3 assets without explicit permission. After discussing with him, it was impossible to get any kind of agreement. So, this mod is now a patcher and is not distributing any Linkle 3 fileset; it will only apply the changes I made by my own --and they're my work and my exclusive property--. The patcher tool is my property too, as I designed it, coded it and tested it.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Q:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;But why?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;A: &lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Because long arms on Linkle 3 should be addressed, and for more than seven months they didn't did it (but as soon as they do, I will remove it from here). Also, because I think backwards compatibility should have been kept for respect to all the modders who worked/still are working on Linkle using hours and hours and hours of their free time to add new content. Trashing all their work it's not fair. It's wrong. It's an abuse. So if we decided anyway to circumvent Nintendo decision to not allow BOTW to run outside an actual WiiU/Switch, if we decided anyway to circumvent Nintendo decision to not allow BOTW to be modded, if we again circumvented KOEI/Tecmo decision to not include a playable Linkle character on BOTW... well I have the whole right to circunvent and bring backwards compatibility to Linkle for the sake of the hundreds of mods made for Linkle in the past five years.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Q:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;Version 2B?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;A:&lt;/b&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;Yes, it includes a different arms patch made by&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;a class="MemberLink" href="https://gamebanana.com/members/1826204"&gt;EvanM0816&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;(used with authorization)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;as seen on his &lt;a href="https://gamebanana.com/mods/442801"&gt;Stylish Linkle&lt;/a&gt; port. All the other features are exactly the same, just version 2B is using his own solution for the long arms on Linkle 3. It looks slightly different than my patch, so its up to you to try and decide what do you like better.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Q:&lt;/b&gt; Can I distribute the patcher? And the BNP I got?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;A:&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;Yes, it's my program and my work and I'm allowing it. And yes but the Linkle 3 author stated it must only be done outside Gamebanana (this was the only agreement I could get).&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;Q: &lt;/b&gt;Will I get the same as the old Unofficial Linkle 3 Patch?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;b&gt;A:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Yes, in fact version 2 is better as now it's not required to patch any Linkle 3 headgear, and it also solves almost all neck gaps on Linkle 2 mods without editing them. The old one is now labeled as version 1 and it's also available in the downloads section for users having trouble with version 2.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Q: &lt;/b&gt;Will you trash this if these issues are addressed officially?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;A: &lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;Yes, of course. I said it since the very beginning, in the trashed mod page and in the Girly Animation Pack page. In fact, I would love not to spend another single hour on any of this!&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Q: &lt;/b&gt;Will they trash this patch?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;A: &lt;/b&gt;&lt;i&gt;If they do, then I don't understand on what base. And why is Nintendo still allowing this whole site to run as we are doing to their property, exactly the same thing and without having any explicit permission to do it.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;span class="RedColor"&gt;&lt;b&gt;Q! What's this all about?&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;span class="GreenColor"&gt;&lt;i&gt;Ah Jean-Luc, mon captain. Welcome to the very end, of the road that shouldn't have been taken!&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/unofficial_linkle3_patcher_v21a.zip" type="application/zip"/>
